articles.contents:
This is where you link to the other files, which are in a content folder in the main directory.
Make sure the name of the folder does not have an underscore in it.
And, when you create and update the file, you need to reknit it!.

De Rmd filer der ligger i websidens root mappe bliver automatisk “knit’et”! På denne webside er det content.Rmd, lab01.Rmd, lab02.Rmd og index.Rmd.

articles.title: Web forside
articles.contents:
Dette er min forside.
Dette er en simpel hjemmeside lavet med R Markdown og distill, der egner sig til webside og blog. Hvis man bruger Netlify som server flyttes _site mappen (her er hele websiden opbygget i html) bare over i Netlify.
Links
The distillery is a blog to build and customize distill sites
rstudio4edu: distill
Distill for R Markdown
distill for R Markdown
RStudio AI Blog
Building a website using R {distill}
Sharing on Short Notice: How to Get Your Materials Online With R Markdown
Themes
You can’t always get what you want: Note that Distill does not give you the option to use a floating TOC, change color themes, use code_download nor code_folding as you can in a regular .Rmd site. Another weird thing worth pointing out is that the only way to get a TOC on the index.Rmd page is to specify one globally within the _site.yml. It cannot be added individually to the index page alone (but it can be to other Distill pages).

articles.title: Lab 1
articles.contents:
R Markdown
This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com.
When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:


summary(cars)


     speed           dist       
 Min.   : 4.0   Min.   :  2.00  
 1st Qu.:12.0   1st Qu.: 26.00  
 Median :15.0   Median : 36.00  
 Mean   :15.4   Mean   : 42.98  
 3rd Qu.:19.0   3rd Qu.: 56.00  
 Max.   :25.0   Max.   :120.00  

Including Plots
You can also embed plots, for example:



Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.
